---
title: Italian Hoagie Salad with Prosciutto with Creamy Italian Dressing & Croutons
description: It’s always tasty in Philadelphia! Well, it is if you’re eating what they call a hoagie (aka. a sub, a hero, a grinder). But if you’re looking for a lighter salad option, have we got a great lunch idea for you! We take all the fillings—prosciutto, bell pepper, tomato, cucumber—and toss them with crisp lettuce, creamy Italian dressing, a sprinkle of oregano, and crushed croutons on top for crunch. That’s right: Philly is in the house.
